 a later reader to sort deterministically.\n\n## Privacy Posture\n\n`agentlog sync` should be explicit in the first implementation. Captured\ntranscripts are redacted, but they can still reveal sensitive project context,\nprompting strategy, file names inside tool commands, and architectural details.\n\nThe command help and human output should make the remote exchange clear without\nturning the POC into a warning framework. Use wording along these lines:\n\n```text\nSync redacted agentlog metadata with a Git remote.\n```\n\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T17:13:08.065Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}